HEADWORD: Peritreme
<hw>Per"i*treme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>peri-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a hole.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>That part of the integument of an insect which
surrounds the spiracles.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The edge of the
aperture of a univalve shell.</def>⟦br⟧
